Creates a Trusted Origin.

This resource allows you to create and configure an Trusted Origin.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}

{{% example csharp %}}
```csharp
using Pulumi;
using Okta = Pulumi.Okta;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var example = new Okta.TrustedOrigin.Origin("example", new Okta.TrustedOrigin.OriginArgs
        {
            Origin = "https://example.com",
            Scopes = 
            {
                "CORS",
            },
        });
    }

}
```

{{% /example %}}

{{% example go %}}
```go
package main

import (
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-okta/sdk/v2/go/okta/trustedorigin"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v2/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		_, err := trustedorigin.NewOrigin(ctx, "example", &trustedorigin.OriginArgs{
			Origin: pulumi.String("https://example.com"),
			Scopes: pulumi.StringArray{
				pulumi.String("CORS"),
			},
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}
```
